ANTIOCH ASSOCIATES (Lindgren), San Francisco, CA

 

Lists:  {Large general}

    I:   numbered lists in one series were published both

independently and as advertisements in The Celator, apparently

occurring as either the one or the other, or both simultaneously.

The separata are characteristically n.d., but their year can

often be deduced from the appearance of adjacent numbers in The

Celator.

   * The numbers held in this library in The Celator are

distinguished below by the month of issue in brackets, e.g.

"[Jun]".

 

   II:   numbered lists not in I were published independently. 

They are not the same as the lists of series I, though they bear the same numbers.

DUPRIEZ, Ch., Brussels

   * from at least no 83 onwards the issues are overtly numbered,

lists and auction catalogues in a single series.  The lists

are n.d., and can only be located within the overt chronology

of the auction catalogues.  Also, the numeration of both lists

and auction catalogues is not simple, given the insertion of

supplements, so named;  or of numbers repeated with bis or ter, or

with successive letters of the alphabet.  And some late lists are

unnumbered (and n.d.) anyway.

 

  have ordinal numbers 83-92, 94-103, 105-116, 118, 120
